This paper is about improving the performance of neural machine translation (NMT) models through data selection techniques. The paper specifically focuses on one data selection approach called Feature Decay Algorithms (FDA) and proposes the use of an approximated target-side in addition to the source-side when selecting suitable sentence-pairs for training a model. Given this focus on NMT and data selection, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). Other likely sub-categories include cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.CV (Computer Vision), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
